<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#000080"><FONT color="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;Subject:&nbsp;Curscale armor (kunark)</font></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
<tr>
    <td  bgcolor="#DCDCDC" width="100%" valign="top"><tt><font color="#000000">
Author:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:&#97;&#114;&#97;&#103;&#111;&#110;&#100;&#49;&#64;&#97;&#111;&#108;&#46;&#99;&#111;&#109;?subject=Curscale armor (kunark)">Kommodoe of Bristlebane</a>&nbsp;(sdn-ar-001ncraleP058.dialsprint.net)<br>
Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;06-26-2000 16:03<br><br>
    This quest is GREAT for newbie iksars, and it yeilds useful armor, along witha substantial amount of exp through level 5, and half the time over a gold in coin. not to mention, it's incredibly easy.<BR>
1)Hail Klok Mogruk, who is inside the Haggle Baron, usually facing the entrance to the Court of Pain(monk guild). he tell you that you couldn't hope to afford bristle silk(if you ask him about it), but that if you helped he could give you some curscale armor.he'll give you a little 8-slot bag and tell you to fill it with Scaled Curskins, looted off the annoying little scaled wolf pups found in abundance outside town in the feild of bone.<BR>
2) i suggest that you get about 3 backpacks full of scaled curskins(counting the one he gives you) to give to him. once you have gathered enough, open the bag he gave you and hit "combine". give the "full curskin bag" to Klok Mugruk. he'll give you a random peice of curscale armor, some coin, and good exp.then say you will [perform the small service] again and fill the bag with you additional skins. repeat. the armor is slightly better than patchwork, and has bonuses to resistance. do this quest over and over, and you will have fairly decent armor(for a newbie) and you'll level very fast. if you get a copy of a piece you already have, auction it or sell it to a vendor.<BR>
i always carry around a full suit (exceptionally light, great for monks) just in case.<BR>
<BR>
Kommodoe, Iksar Shaman of the 8th level<BR>
Bristlebane server</font></tt></td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
